ogens. Additionally, Calymmodon gracilis has been shown to have anti-inflammatory properties, making it a treatment option for arthritis and joint pain. Its antimicrobial properties also aid in wound healing and infection prevention. Furthermore, the plant's antioxidants help combat oxidative stress, contributing to the prevention of cancer and neurodegenerative diseases.", "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Calymmodon gracilis are flavonoids, phenolic acids, triterpenoids, and alkaloids. Flavonoids like kaempferol, quercetin, and isorhapontigenin present in Calymmodon gracilis exhibit antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties, which contribute to its healing effects. Phenolic acids like ferulic acid and caffeic acid have been shown to possess antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory activities, while triterpenoids like ursolic acid and oleanolic acid display anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Alkaloids present in Calymmodon gracilis such as berberine and palmatine have been found to exhibit antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and immunomodulatory activities. These bioactive compounds in Calymmodon gracilis contribute to its potential therapeutic applications, including wound healing, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties.", "properties": [{"name": "antioxidant", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 138, "total_score": 2760}, {"name": "antimicrobial", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 123, "total_score": 2460}, {"name": "anti-inflammatory", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 113, "total_score": 2260}, {"name": "antifungal", "mentions": 14, "confidence_score": 81, "total_score": 1134}, {"name": "analgesic", "mentions": 17, "confidence_score": 57, "total_score": 969}, {"name": "antibacterial", "mentions": 10, "confidence_score": 57, "total_score": 570}, {"name": "wound healing", "mentions": 7, "confidence_score": 48, "total_score": 336}, {"name": "antiviral", "mentions": 14, "confidence_score": 42